_1.ogg\" title=\"providence pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ˈprɑːvɪdəns/</span></div></span> <div class=\"variants\" id=\"providence_vgs_1\" htag=\"div\" type=\"vs\" hclass=\"variants\">(also <span class=\"v-g\" id=\"providence_vg_1\"><span class=\"v\" id=\"providence_v_1\">Providence</span></span>)</div> <span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[uncountable]</span> <span class=\"labels\" hclass=\"labels\" htag=\"span\">(formal)</span><span class=\"jumplinks\"><a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/providence_1#providence_idmgs_1\" title=\"Idioms definition\"><span class=\"jumplink\" name=\"Idioms\" href=\"providence_idmgs_1\">Idioms</span></a> </span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" hclass=\"sense\" fkcefr=\"c2\" id=\"providence_sng_1\" htag=\"li\"><a class=\"open oup_icons\" title=\"Add to My Word Lists\"><span class=\"star-btn\" aria-hidden=\"true\">​</span></a><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" hclass=\"def\" htag=\"span\">God, or a force that some people believe controls our lives and the things that happen to us, usually in a way that protects us</span></span> <span class=\"xrefs\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"xrefs\" xt=\"nsyn\"><span class=\"prefix\">synonym</span> <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/fate\" title=\"fate definition\"><span class=\"xr-g\" href=\"fate_e\" bord=\"n\"><span class=\"xh\">fate</span></span></a></span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">to trust in divine providence</span></li><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">She